cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel training approach that involves label propagation and uncertainty estimates, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions incorporating natural language processing techniques, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes experiments on image data, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
